<div id="review_1470404470" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1470404470" />
    <a title="Betül" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/18248241-bet-l"><img alt="Betül" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1636922424p2/18248241.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1470404470?book_show_action=true">Dec 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Betül" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Betül" href="/user/show/18248241-bet-l">Betül</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1470404470" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6069061237992564385">Why did i wait too much to read this book? Honestly, i&apos;m angry at myself. Yalom&apos;s prose is so smooth, almost perfect; sometimes i felt like reading Tolstoy or Dostoyevsky. What i&apos;ve learned: Take your life&apos; s responsibility so you can accept it and find meaning in it, once you can take responsibility, find meaning in it and be &quot;me&quot; before being &quot;we&quot;, you can feel that you are free. Don&apos;t forget that your experiences are authentic -personal- don&apos;t try to make better someone depending on your own </span>
  <span id="freeText6069061237992564385" style="display:none">Why did i wait too much to read this book? Honestly, i'm angry at myself. Yalom's prose is so smooth, almost perfect; sometimes i felt like reading Tolstoy or Dostoyevsky. What i've learned: Take your life' s responsibility so you can accept it and find meaning in it, once you can take responsibility, find meaning in it and be "me" before being "we", you can feel that you are free. Don't forget that your experiences are authentic -personal- don't try to make better someone depending on your own experiences. And the final words, i don't know have you heard this before, but i really admire: "Offer a suffering friend a resting place, but take care it be a hard bed."</span>
  <a data-text-id="6069061237992564385" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


